It&#39;s because you&#39;ve created instances of the LDAP module, so the LDAP-Group attribute&#39;s name has changed.  There are a few ways to solve this, but the easiest is to instruct the LDAP module to use the same attribute for all its instances, and then have it retrieve the complete membership listing.

For each LDAP module, uncomment and set [cache_attribute][1] to be the same.  This can just be set to &#39;LDAP-Group&#39; if you want.

Then, again, for each LDAP module, uncomment and set [cacheable_dn][2] to &#39;yes&#39;.

You may need to call rlb_ldap to pre-populate the group information, before you attempt any group checks, else the group check will just hit one LDAP or or the other, and you won&#39;t get redundancy.

If you&#39;re using EAP, and pulling out LDAP information in the innter-tunnel you&#39;ll need to store the group membership information in the session state list and restore it before checking membership information again.

To store LDAP group information:

    ldap
    if (ok || updated) {
        update session-state {
            &amp;LDAP-Group += &amp;LDAP-Group[*]
        }
    }

To restore it:

    update request {
        update request {
            &amp;LDAP-Group += &amp;session-state:LDAP-Group[*]
        }
    }

If you&#39;re pulling group information in the inner server, you&#39;ll need to change `update session-state` to `update outer.session-state`.

Another potential issue you may have, is that you&#39;re listing rlb_ldap in post-auth, but aren&#39;t overriding the method.  This means when rlb_ldap is called it will perform its normal post-auth duties, which are modifying a user&#39;s object in the LDAP directory to record the last time then logged in.

To fix this, change your rlb_ldap call to ``rlb_ldap.authorize``, this will result in the group membership information being retrieved instead.

  [1]: https://github.com/FreeRADIUS/freeradius-server/blob/v3.0.x/raddb/mods-available/ldap#L333
  [2]: https://github.com/FreeRADIUS/freeradius-server/blob/v3.0.x/raddb/mods-available/ldap#L327

